External Managers 





 


As a partner, an employer and a manager, Allstate Investments seeks to build value and grow opportunity for all our stakeholders.
Northbrook  |  London  |  Hong Kong




 

Investing from strength.
Allstate Investments has decades of experience pursuing strategies in a broad array of asset classes and geographies in both the public and private markets. No matter what the investment, we remain steadfast in our commitment to deliver strong investment results for each client.
Allstate Investments is comprised of two investment advisors:  Allstate Investments, LLC and Allstate Investment Management Company (AIMCO®), an SEC registered investment advisor. 




Allstate Investments, LLC

Allstate Investments, LLC is proud to serve as the investment manager and advisor for Allstate Insurance Company, Allstate Life Insurance Company and its other domestic insurance company affiliates with approximately $72 billion1 in assets under management. 
We produce solid returns and protect and grow Allstate’s capital to support our clients’ business strategies, ability to pay claims, develop innovative products and services, maintain financial stability, provide financial security for their employees and advance societal goals.
1$72,295 million as of December 31, 2015



Allstate Investment Management Company (AIMCO®)

AIMCO, an SEC registered investment advisor, is Allstate’s investment advisor to its non-domestic insurance company affiliates, non-insurance company affiliates, Allstate’s foundations, Allstate’s pension plans and outside collateralized loan obligations with approximately $5.5 billion2 in assets under management.  For more information on AIMCO®, please see its most recent Form ADV.
2$5.463 million as of December 31, 2015. Excludes the following AIMCO® clients:  Allstate’s pension plans, Allstate’s foundations and the outside collateralized loan obligations.




All of the executive officers of Allstate Investments, LLC are also officers of AIMCO®.  Executive officers of Allstate Investments, LLC perform work for Allstate Investments, LLC and AIMCO®.





Collateralized Loan Obligations (CLO)
Allstate is an experienced participant in the CLO market, both as an investor and a manager. As an investor, we’re active across the capital stack, moving up and down the risk spectrum based on our     assessment of fundamentals and valuations. AIMCO, as the manager for the CLOs, has three deals in the market, is looking to expand its issuance in the future, allowing it to increase its reach in the loan market, continue to leverage its resources and to generate attractive fee income. Our experienced team uses a consistent, disciplined framework for credit assessment that we leverage across the platform of CLOs we invest in, and those that we manage.
For questions regarding AIMCO as the manager of CLO investments, please contact:
Chris Goergen, CFA
          Senior Bank Loan and CLO Portfolio Manager

Investing in and issuing CLOs allow us to leverage our team, expand our reach in the marketplace and generate more value for Allstate.
Mark Pittman, Senior Managing Director





















